WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:19.260
Shh.

2
00:00:20.620 --> 00:00:23.660
Shh. Yeah.

3
00:00:23.730 --> 00:00:25.380
Yeah.

4
00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:28.660
Yeah. easy. Easy.

5
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:32.370
Oh.

6
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:36.910
It's not fair. this life.

7
00:00:42.780 --> 00:00:44.800
I know you deserve better.

8
00:00:49.970 --> 00:00:52.200
Best I can offer you is peace.

9
00:02:44.430 --> 00:02:47.570
The things we lose to keep you fed.

10
00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:53.740
Jesus. that's John Dutton.

11
00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:55.420
Commissioner. you all right?

12
00:04:03.350 --> 00:04:07.720
The state of Montana has
never gauged its progress

13
00:04:07.760 --> 00:04:10.450
by the size of its cities.

14
00:04:10.520 --> 00:04:12.390
We measure our progress

15
00:04:12.450 --> 00:04:14.690
by how those cities impact the people

16
00:04:14.760 --> 00:04:16.830
and the land surrounding them.

17
00:04:16.890 --> 00:04:18.790
the land that feeds them.

18
00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:21.920
provides their water.
nourishes their souls.

19
00:04:22.230 --> 00:04:24.410
This doesn't sound like a
legal argument. Mr. Dutton.

20
00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:26.170
It sounds like a lecture.

21
00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:28.250
Well. it's a summation of
our state constitution.

22
00:04:28.270 --> 00:04:30.319
which clearly states
that land preservation

23
00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:31.970
and property rights take precedence

24
00:04:32.110 --> 00:04:33.380
over public expansion.

25
00:04:33.400 --> 00:04:35.610
The constitution clearly denotes

26
00:04:35.620 --> 00:04:37.310
the state's right to eminent domain

27
00:04:37.380 --> 00:04:39.550
and grants the authority
to condemn property

28
00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:40.620
for the public good.

29
00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:42.120
For essential public services

30
00:04:42.150 --> 00:04:44.320
like hospitals. schools. highways...

31
00:04:44.390 --> 00:04:45.990
not housing developments.

32
00:04:46.060 --> 00:04:48.520
Housing is essential.

33
00:04:48.590 --> 00:04:51.190
Bozeman has doubled in size in a decade.

34
00:04:51.260 --> 00:04:53.000
We're 30 miles away.

35
00:04:53.130 --> 00:04:57.030
and our population is less
than it was 40 years ago.

36
00:04:57.130 --> 00:04:59.930
- Why?
- Because their fence guarantees

37
00:04:59.940 --> 00:05:01.280
we don't grow.

38
00:05:01.700 --> 00:05:03.670
Stagnation is death for a town.

39
00:05:03.680 --> 00:05:05.540
and the Duttons are the ones killing it.

40
00:05:05.860 --> 00:05:08.540
Well. poetic if it were true.

41
00:05:08.580 --> 00:05:10.680
since a Dutton founded the town.

42
00:05:10.750 --> 00:05:13.340
As it stands. the defendant is correct.

43
00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:16.000
Our land use laws are quite clear.

44
00:05:16.140 --> 00:05:18.080
For this commission to
grant eminent domain.

45
00:05:18.120 --> 00:05:21.890
you must show public need. not desire.

46
00:05:21.960 --> 00:05:23.660
I think that's enough posturing.

47
00:05:23.730 --> 00:05:25.700
- Let's put it to a vote.
- The plaintiff hasn't shown

48
00:05:25.710 --> 00:05:27.190
any legal imperative for a vote.

49
00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:28.900
so this case is dismissed.

50
00:05:34.100 --> 00:05:36.180
It's 30.000 acres. Jamie.

51
00:05:36.610 --> 00:05:39.209
That isn't a fraction of the ranch.

52
00:05:39.210 --> 00:05:42.710
Okay. look. you can
harvest the timber first.

53
00:05:42.780 --> 00:05:45.110
no environmental review. nothing.

54
00:05:45.210 --> 00:05:47.840
You can cut every tree to the root.

55
00:05:48.420 --> 00:05:49.920
You want to suggest to my father

56
00:05:49.990 --> 00:05:51.920
that he clear-cut his land. be my guest.

57
00:05:51.990 --> 00:05:53.400
You're a braver man than me.

58
00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:55.180
Just mention it. Jamie.

59
00:05:56.330 --> 00:05:58.260
The town grows. or it dies.

60
00:05:58.330 --> 00:06:00.560
Well. maybe it should grow... up.

61
00:06:00.630 --> 00:06:03.800
Condos. Alan. like they
have in San Francisco.

62
00:06:04.670 --> 00:06:06.840
Condos?

63
00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:09.710
Who wants to live in a condo in Montana?

64
00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:24.220
I don't know how you're gonna
get 'em out by yourself.

65
00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:26.500
Don't have to get 'em all out.

66
00:06:28.020 --> 00:06:29.690
Just that stallion.

67
00:06:29.760 --> 00:06:32.190
Once he's gone. the rest
will leave on their own.

68
00:06:32.260 --> 00:06:35.100
Best of luck. That bastard
kicked my truck door so hard.

69
00:06:35.140 --> 00:06:37.770
we had to use a crowbar to get it open.

70
00:06:37.830 --> 00:06:40.200
That damn mustang's done more
in one week to stop drilling

71
00:06:40.270 --> 00:06:42.400
than every environmental
group in the state.

72
00:06:42.470 --> 00:06:45.040
Maybe I should just leave
him where he is then.

73
00:06:47.980 --> 00:06:50.380
Where'd you find this guy?

74
00:06:50.450 --> 00:06:52.410
Yellow pages.

75
00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:54.550
Ad says he works with problem horses.

76
00:06:54.620 --> 00:06:56.100
Oh. this'll be interesting.

77
00:06:58.620 --> 00:06:59.890
Kid's fucking crazy.

78
00:07:04.930 --> 00:07:06.860
Yeah. uh...

79
00:07:07.360 --> 00:07:09.700
sure is building something.

80
00:07:12.830 --> 00:07:14.970
- Beth.
- Of course he didn't.

81
00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:16.940
He couldn't find his
ass with both hands.

82
00:07:17.010 --> 00:07:18.870
- Bob... Bob needs you.
- Give me a minute.

83
00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:20.360
I don't think he has a minute.

84
00:07:21.980 --> 00:07:23.919
God damn it. Bob. I didn't come here

85
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:25.500
to do business with these people.

86
00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:27.080
I came here to do business with you.

87
00:07:27.100 --> 00:07:30.360
I can hear you screaming
halfway down the hall. Craig.

88
00:07:36.190 --> 00:07:38.490
I thought we were gonna try
and work this out. Bob.

89
00:07:38.560 --> 00:07:39.806
We've been trying to work this out

90
00:07:39.830 --> 00:07:41.540
for three hours. Craig.

91
00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:44.600
This is the alternative.

92
00:07:44.670 --> 00:07:46.100
We don't want to merge.

93
00:07:46.160 --> 00:07:47.970
No one wants to merge with you.

94
00:07:48.040 --> 00:07:49.600
You have a three-to-one debt ratio.

95
00:07:49.620 --> 00:07:51.500
It'd be easier to sell VCRs.

96
00:07:52.660 --> 00:07:54.539
I'm not gonna be bullied by your

97
00:07:54.540 --> 00:07:56.540
hatchet man. Bob.

98
00:07:57.110 --> 00:07:58.710
We will pull our funds.

99
00:07:58.780 --> 00:08:01.920
and we will take our business
down the street to Chase.

100
00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:04.380
We're just asking you to
suspend the dividend.

101
00:08:04.440 --> 00:08:05.680
And kill the stock!

102
00:08:05.700 --> 00:08:06.990
What do you think's gonna happen

103
00:08:07.060 --> 00:08:09.820
when I dump our 18%
share tomorrow morning?

104
00:08:10.360 --> 00:08:11.630
I'll tell you what.

105
00:08:11.690 --> 00:08:13.530
The stock will drop below 10.

106
00:08:13.600 --> 00:08:15.530
SEC will suspend trading.

107
00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:18.540
and every creditor you
have will file on you.

108
00:08:18.580 --> 00:08:21.670
Your company will be
chapter 11 by Friday.

109
00:08:21.740 --> 00:08:23.810
and since we're your largest creditors.

110
00:08:23.870 --> 00:08:26.980
I can promise you there'll
be no negotiating then.

111
00:08:27.040 --> 00:08:30.550
I will be CEO of IL Energy by Monday.

112
00:08:30.610 --> 00:08:32.820
I will fire every fucking employee.

113
00:08:32.920 --> 00:08:35.750
Then I will sell your leases
and equipment to Chevron

114
00:08:35.820 --> 00:08:39.490
for 30¢ on the dollar. and you. buddy.

115
00:08:39.550 --> 00:08:41.690
you will have the unique distinction

116
00:08:41.760 --> 00:08:43.630
of being the only drilling company

117
00:08:43.640 --> 00:08:46.060
to go bankrupt in the largest oil boom

118
00:08:46.070 --> 00:08:47.680
of the last century.

119
00:08:48.940 --> 00:08:50.820
Won't that look good on a resume?

120
00:08:51.730 --> 00:08:55.840
I started this company in my garage.

121
00:08:55.920 --> 00:08:57.199
That's where it's gonna end up

122
00:08:57.200 --> 00:08:58.540
if you don't suspend the dividend

123
00:08:58.610 --> 00:09:00.840
and allow us to assume management.

124
00:09:02.680 --> 00:09:04.020
Don't look at him.

125
00:09:04.750 --> 00:09:06.300
You're dealing with me now.

126
00:09:08.680 --> 00:09:10.200
So what's it gonna be?

127
00:09:11.480 --> 00:09:13.760
Are we restructuring
your company tomorrow

128
00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:15.260
or killing it?

129
00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:22.360
Good.

130
00:09:22.430 --> 00:09:24.170
You made the right choice. Craig.

131
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:30.670
We'll get you through this.

132
00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:36.450
Bitch.

133
00:09:42.450 --> 00:09:44.080
I just saved your house.

134
00:09:44.750 --> 00:09:46.800
I put your kids through college.

135
00:09:47.700 --> 00:09:50.560
Maybe you should say
something more appropriate.

136
00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:56.030
Thank you.

137
00:09:57.370 --> 00:09:58.740
You're welcome.

138
00:11:11.810 --> 00:11:13.420
Daddy!

139
00:11:13.540 --> 00:11:14.610
Hey. buddy.

140
00:11:18.710 --> 00:11:20.780
Bet it was fun putting
him in the trailer.

141
00:11:20.850 --> 00:11:22.720
Yeah. they call him a tornado.

142
00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:25.690
How are you planning on getting him out?

143
00:11:25.750 --> 00:11:27.320
I'm just making this up as I go. babe.

144
00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:32.460
I'd step back a bit
further if I were you.

145
00:11:36.230 --> 00:11:37.330
It's all right.

146
00:11:38.800 --> 00:11:40.570
I know it don't seem like it. but it is.

147
00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:45.540
Easy.

148
00:11:45.610 --> 00:11:47.810
Easy.

149
00:11:47.880 --> 00:11:50.050
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

150
00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:52.280
Easy. easy. That's it.

151
00:11:52.350 --> 00:11:53.400
That's it.

152
00:11:55.250 --> 00:11:56.850
Hey.

153
00:11:57.990 --> 00:11:59.690
Whoa... whoa.

154
00:11:59.760 --> 00:12:01.290
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

155
00:12:01.360 --> 00:12:03.020
You kids get back!

156
00:12:03.040 --> 00:12:04.590
Hey. hey. hey.

157
00:12:06.530 --> 00:12:08.180
That's it. that's it. Come on.

158
00:12:10.740 --> 00:12:12.200
It's all right. It's all right.

159
00:12:17.740 --> 00:12:19.210
Can I pet him?

160
00:12:19.270 --> 00:12:21.840
Sure. son. in about a year.

161
00:12:21.910 --> 00:12:24.850
No fear in this one.
He got that from you.

162
00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:27.120
You mean no common sense.
He got that from you.

163
00:12:28.280 --> 00:12:30.959
Well. I suppose your homework

164
00:12:30.960 --> 00:12:32.680
is in the kitchen doing itself.

165
00:12:38.230 --> 00:12:40.820
Oh. he's gonna be fun to break.

166
00:12:42.330 --> 00:12:45.140
Well. holler at me if you need my help.

167
00:12:46.470 --> 00:12:48.000
Free tomorrow?

168
00:12:48.070 --> 00:12:49.770
Could use a hand.

169
00:12:49.840 --> 00:12:51.770
Yeah. sure.

170
00:12:51.840 --> 00:12:53.560
Bring a horse.

171
00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:55.340
Just not that one.

172
00:13:01.320 --> 00:13:04.320
Wow. My brother actually talked to you.

173
00:13:04.390 --> 00:13:06.400
Well. that was progress.

174
00:13:06.860 --> 00:13:08.540
Yeah. it was something.

175
00:13:08.990 --> 00:13:11.050
I got parent conferences tonight.

176
00:13:11.060 --> 00:13:12.930
so you're on Tate patrol.

177
00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.200
All right.

178
00:13:16.830 --> 00:13:18.700
I wonder what he's thinking.

179
00:13:19.530 --> 00:13:22.440
Well. he's probably thinking
I took his freedom.

180
00:13:22.500 --> 00:13:24.340
Well. he's right.

181
00:13:26.840 --> 00:13:28.240
Supper's ready.

182
00:13:42.920 --> 00:13:44.630
Ah. damn it.

183
00:13:46.430 --> 00:13:49.970
Your mother was always better at this.

184
00:13:51.100 --> 00:13:53.140
Hey. you know who's really good at it?

185
00:13:54.700 --> 00:13:56.840
- Doctors.
- Yeah.

186
00:13:56.910 --> 00:13:59.140
Should have done that yesterday.

187
00:13:59.240 --> 00:14:02.040
Here. let me do it. Let me do it.

188
00:14:03.780 --> 00:14:06.400
All right. Alan asked me
to mention it. so I will.

189
00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:09.520
They'd allow us to harvest
the timber before the...

190
00:14:09.580 --> 00:14:10.750
No.

191
00:14:11.920 --> 00:14:14.220
- The answer's no.
- Yeah.

192
00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:15.740
Can I do this?

193
00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:18.530
Yeah.

194
00:14:18.590 --> 00:14:21.760
When you say no. it must be
the death of the question.

195
00:14:21.830 --> 00:14:23.000
Mm-hmm. I understand.

196
00:14:23.070 --> 00:14:24.530
If there's even a hint of maybe.

197
00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:26.010
the questions won't stop until they find

198
00:14:26.030 --> 00:14:27.540
something you can't say no to.

199
00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:28.970
Mm.

200
00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:34.556
You got to learn when to think

201
00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:35.880
like a lawyer. you understand?

202
00:14:35.940 --> 00:14:37.800
And when to think like a landowner.

203
00:14:38.210 --> 00:14:40.180
Or a lawyer's all you're ever gonna be.

204
00:14:43.390 --> 00:14:45.020
Yeah.

205
00:14:45.090 --> 00:14:46.940
Well. I'll say this. You...

206
00:14:47.920 --> 00:14:49.990
You got your mother's hands.

207
00:15:00.470 --> 00:15:01.870
Hey.

208
00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:03.470
I told them no.

209
00:15:09.440 --> 00:15:11.580
Hey. I said you wouldn't consider it.

210
00:15:12.750 --> 00:15:15.220
Should you consider it? Absolutely.

211
00:15:17.380 --> 00:15:19.760
We could use the money and the
leverage that comes with it.

212
00:15:19.800 --> 00:15:21.590
You're not coming. Dad?

213
00:15:23.860 --> 00:15:26.120
No. I got a meeting in Bozeman.

214
00:15:28.100 --> 00:15:30.280
Why don't you take your
badge out with you today?

215
00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:32.430
Take a rifle too.

216
00:15:32.500 --> 00:15:34.540
I mean. they won't give us
any trouble over strays.

217
00:15:34.570 --> 00:15:36.350
I mean. hell. they'll probably
help us round them up.

218
00:15:36.370 --> 00:15:38.640
Well. the badge is for the
ranchers riding with you.

219
00:15:39.210 --> 00:15:41.320
It'll keep them from
bringing home any extras.

220
00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:45.980
Did you hear me?

221
00:15:51.450 --> 00:15:53.940
Leverage is knowing if someone had...

222
00:15:54.360 --> 00:15:56.360
all the money in the world...

223
00:15:58.330 --> 00:16:01.060
This is what they'd buy.

224
00:17:18.820 --> 00:17:20.060
Senator.

225
00:17:21.030 --> 00:17:22.199
I'm sorry I'm late.

226
00:17:22.200 --> 00:17:24.419
I wanted to see the reservation first.

227
00:17:24.420 --> 00:17:26.000
Did you enjoy your tour?

228
00:17:26.090 --> 00:17:28.050
No. no. I did not.

229
00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:30.259
Well. it's good that you took it.

230
00:17:30.260 --> 00:17:33.500
Inequity must be
witnessed to be changed.

231
00:17:33.590 --> 00:17:35.629
Please have a seat.

232
00:17:35.630 --> 00:17:36.840
Oh.

233
00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:40.770
I can't imagine all your mother overcame

234
00:17:40.780 --> 00:17:42.140
just to raise you here.

235
00:17:42.220 --> 00:17:43.639
I never met my mother.

236
00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:45.420
and I wasn't raised here.

237
00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:48.139
Till I was 18. I thought I was Mexican

238
00:17:48.140 --> 00:17:50.180
even though I didn't look Mexican

239
00:17:50.390 --> 00:17:51.960
and I didn't feel Mexican.

240
00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:55.260
if one can feel their heritage.
which I believe one can.

241
00:17:55.520 --> 00:17:59.060
When I turned 18. my adoption
records were unsealed.

242
00:17:59.390 --> 00:18:01.469
and imagine my surprise.

243
00:18:01.470 --> 00:18:03.679
I confronted my adopted parents.

244
00:18:03.680 --> 00:18:06.580
who said they lied to protect me.

245
00:18:08.930 --> 00:18:10.700
They said as a Mexican.

246
00:18:11.060 --> 00:18:13.980
I would face discrimination. sure.

247
00:18:14.850 --> 00:18:18.389
but as an Indian. I would know a hatred

248
00:18:18.390 --> 00:18:21.560
that had to be endured
to be fully understood.

249
00:18:22.240 --> 00:18:24.900
They thought they were giving
me a better chance at life.

250
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:28.979
That's this nation's policy toward us.

251
00:18:28.980 --> 00:18:30.980
always has been.

252
00:18:31.680 --> 00:18:34.559
If we want a better
life. all we have to do

253
00:18:34.560 --> 00:18:36.420
is stop being Indian.

254
00:18:36.520 --> 00:18:38.440
I'm gonna change that policy.

255
00:18:38.620 --> 00:18:42.200
My people are the only ones
that can change that policy.

256
00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.459
The gambler's money is like a river.

257
00:18:48.460 --> 00:18:52.660
flowing one way... our way.

258
00:18:52.900 --> 00:18:54.960
Senator. you've never driven a road

259
00:18:55.180 --> 00:18:58.659
or walked a trail or skied
a mountain in Montana

260
00:18:58.660 --> 00:19:00.560
that didn't belong to my people first.

261
00:19:01.960 --> 00:19:03.600
This nation doesn't
want to give it back?

262
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:06.200
So be it.

263
00:19:06.830 --> 00:19:08.640
We'll buy it back...

264
00:19:09.690 --> 00:19:11.149
with their money.

265
00:19:11.150 --> 00:19:12.900
So what do you want from me?

266
00:19:15.190 --> 00:19:17.420
I want you to help me spend it.

267
00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:20.359
Come.

268
00:19:20.360 --> 00:19:22.360
Meet the people we're saving.

269
00:19:24.740 --> 00:19:28.630
Ladies and gentlemen. let's
welcome the new chairman

270
00:19:28.640 --> 00:19:32.729
of Broken Rock. Thomas Rainwater!

271
00:19:39.650 --> 00:19:41.189
What about water and power?

272
00:19:41.190 --> 00:19:43.720
You don't need a permit for that?

273
00:19:44.080 --> 00:19:46.840
See. the bank's concern is that
you're gonna break ground.

274
00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:50.499
and the state or the fucking
EPA paper us in lawsuits

275
00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:53.400
because we built a power
plant without a permit.

276
00:19:53.420 --> 00:19:55.760
In the state of Montana.
no permit is required

277
00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:58.190
to build a power source
for a mine or a mill.

278
00:19:58.390 --> 00:20:00.510
Now. we'll construct our own mill

279
00:20:00.520 --> 00:20:02.860
that will also allow us to harvest wood

280
00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:04.840
directly from the forest.

281
00:20:05.680 --> 00:20:08.860
cutting our lumber cost by 65%.

282
00:20:11.320 --> 00:20:14.080
Damming the river here
will generate enough power

283
00:20:14.160 --> 00:20:15.850
to light every home in the subdivision.

284
00:20:15.980 --> 00:20:18.390
Now. this is a self-sustaining community

285
00:20:18.840 --> 00:20:23.360
30 miles from the most pristine
wilderness in North America.

286
00:20:23.720 --> 00:20:25.930
Now. if you don't see
the potential in that.

287
00:20:25.960 --> 00:20:27.379
we need another bank.

288
00:20:27.380 --> 00:20:29.780
We see the potential. I just...

289
00:20:30.970 --> 00:20:34.139
There are no restrictions
on damming a river?

290
00:20:34.140 --> 00:20:35.980
Beavers do it all the time.

291
00:20:36.390 --> 00:20:38.480
On our land it's our river.

292
00:20:38.770 --> 00:20:40.780
Now. this isn't California. gentlemen.

293
00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:43.360
This is Montana.

294
00:20:46.390 --> 00:20:48.880
We can do whatever we want.

295
00:21:16.180 --> 00:21:18.179
My name's Ted.

296
00:21:18.180 --> 00:21:19.720
Where are you from?

297
00:21:20.520 --> 00:21:22.420
Really?

298
00:21:22.440 --> 00:21:24.099
I've been here a week. You're
the first person I've met

299
00:21:24.100 --> 00:21:26.080
who's actually from here.

300
00:21:27.580 --> 00:21:29.300
Can I buy you another drink?

301
00:21:29.520 --> 00:21:30.980
Why not?

302
00:21:31.930 --> 00:21:34.080
Hey. Dalton. give me another one.

303
00:21:34.180 --> 00:21:36.500
You don't live here anymore.
though. not dressed like that.

304
00:21:37.350 --> 00:21:40.160
You came back for a family reunion.

305
00:21:40.280 --> 00:21:44.020
No. no. those never happen
at home for some reason.

306
00:21:44.060 --> 00:21:47.600
Let's see. Bozeman is a college town.

307
00:21:48.390 --> 00:21:51.620
so I'm gonna say a school reunion.

308
00:21:52.200 --> 00:21:55.600
class of... 2006.

309
00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:58.300
Am I close?

310
00:21:59.850 --> 00:22:01.720
Do you feel close. Ted?

311
00:22:02.310 --> 00:22:04.780
Ah. it feels like I'm getting close.

312
00:22:04.880 --> 00:22:06.970
My turn.

313
00:22:07.850 --> 00:22:09.309
You're in real estate or something

314
00:22:09.310 --> 00:22:11.389
equally as unimportant. married.

315
00:22:11.390 --> 00:22:12.889
couple of kids. one on the way.

316
00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:15.240
That was your excuse to come out here.

317
00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:17.799
Need the break. Work. family life.

318
00:22:17.800 --> 00:22:19.219
It's so demanding.

319
00:22:19.220 --> 00:22:21.880
A little fresh air. a little "me time."

320
00:22:22.270 --> 00:22:24.659
You came alone 'cause none of
your friends could afford it.

321
00:22:24.660 --> 00:22:26.389
and those who do. they...
they have wives

322
00:22:26.390 --> 00:22:28.599
a lot smarter than yours
'cause let's be honest. Ted.

323
00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:30.880
you didn't come here to fish.

324
00:22:30.920 --> 00:22:32.389
You're hunting.

325
00:22:32.390 --> 00:22:33.859
That's why you're sitting in a bar

326
00:22:33.860 --> 00:22:35.360
instead of standing in a river.

327
00:22:37.520 --> 00:22:38.969
Who the hell are you to judge me?

328
00:22:38.970 --> 00:22:40.560
I ain't judging you. buddy.

329
00:22:40.620 --> 00:22:42.000
Morning. gentlemen.

330
00:22:42.100 --> 00:22:44.139
I'm hunting too.

331
00:22:44.140 --> 00:22:46.340
just not hunting you.

332
00:22:46.390 --> 00:22:48.020
What's wrong with me?

333
00:22:48.970 --> 00:22:51.320
You look like a real soft fuck. Ted.

334
00:22:52.740 --> 00:22:54.760
All you city boys do.

335
00:22:59.560 --> 00:23:02.240
Gentlemen. mind if I join you?

336
00:23:04.140 --> 00:23:07.020
They even got the barb wire tore down.

337
00:23:07.270 --> 00:23:09.310
That is our property. god damn it.

338
00:23:09.520 --> 00:23:10.639
Can't hear ya.

339
00:23:10.640 --> 00:23:12.500
Come about 2 feet closer.

340
00:23:12.600 --> 00:23:15.139
- You think I won't?
- I think you shouldn't.

341
00:23:15.140 --> 00:23:17.820
but coming on our land
is bred into you people.

342
00:23:18.020 --> 00:23:19.960
I've had enough of your shit.

343
00:23:21.390 --> 00:23:22.880
Let me tell you something...

344
00:23:25.390 --> 00:23:27.530
When those cattle walked onto our land.

345
00:23:27.540 --> 00:23:30.060
they became our cattle
to do as we please.

346
00:23:30.180 --> 00:23:33.120
Whatever happens next
happens to you first.

347
00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:39.120
Son of a bitch.

348
00:23:43.240 --> 00:23:44.260
Back up.

349
00:23:44.270 --> 00:23:47.000
You should respect your betters.

350
00:24:05.390 --> 00:24:07.389
Boy. you sure made a mess of this.

351
00:24:07.390 --> 00:24:09.500
It was a mess when I got here.

352
00:24:10.180 --> 00:24:11.700
This is a tribal issue. John.

353
00:24:11.760 --> 00:24:13.760
Livestock commission's
got no authority here.

354
00:24:13.840 --> 00:24:16.060
Those look like livestock to me.

355
00:24:17.020 --> 00:24:18.979
The Chief's at Commencement.

356
00:24:18.980 --> 00:24:20.980
but I'm calling the shots.

357
00:24:21.680 --> 00:24:25.850
I'm impressed you said that
with a straight face. Ben.

358
00:24:29.500 --> 00:24:32.780
Cattle wandered onto res land. John.

359
00:24:32.840 --> 00:24:34.179
Yeah. well.

360
00:24:34.180 --> 00:24:35.389
cattle don't know the difference

361
00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:36.840
between your land and ours.

362
00:24:36.970 --> 00:24:40.140
Neither did we till the
government showed us. Ha.

363
00:24:40.390 --> 00:24:42.860
Now I guess we're showing you.

364
00:24:43.980 --> 00:24:47.780
I argued against it.
but the new chief...

365
00:24:49.140 --> 00:24:50.840
Hungry for a fight. this one.

366
00:24:51.310 --> 00:24:53.460
God damn it. I just...

367
00:24:54.620 --> 00:24:57.760
I just don't see how anyone
gains from all this. Felix.

368
00:24:57.820 --> 00:25:01.100
I don't either. but he
don't think like me.

369
00:25:02.200 --> 00:25:04.040
Grew up in Denver.

370
00:25:04.140 --> 00:25:06.460
went to some big university.

371
00:25:07.560 --> 00:25:09.560
Now he thinks like you.

372
00:25:19.060 --> 00:25:22.360
I'll keep 'em here as
long as I can. John.

373
00:25:24.850 --> 00:25:27.100
I'll bring up hay so they don't wander.

374
00:25:30.930 --> 00:25:31.939
Lee!

375
00:25:31.940 --> 00:25:33.460
I got to go.

376
00:25:34.820 --> 00:25:36.420
Clear everyone out.

377
00:25:38.260 --> 00:25:40.780
You know. there was barbed
wire on this fence a week ago.

378
00:25:43.880 --> 00:25:45.560
I know. Now clear them out.

379
00:25:46.600 --> 00:25:47.799
Move out!

380
00:25:47.800 --> 00:25:49.280
All right. let's go!

381
00:25:49.320 --> 00:25:52.390
♪ Our flag was still there ♪

382
00:25:52.780 --> 00:25:58.599
♪ Oh. say does that star-spangled ♪

383
00:25:58.600 --> 00:26:04.180
♪ Banner yet wave ♪

384
00:26:04.390 --> 00:26:10.390
♪ O'er the land of the free ♪

385
00:26:10.660 --> 00:26:17.180
♪ And the home of the brave ♪

386
00:26:23.600 --> 00:26:26.000
Ladies and gentlemen. I'd
like to welcome you out

387
00:26:26.020 --> 00:26:29.560
to the 2018 Greater
Montana Livestock Auction.

388
00:26:29.620 --> 00:26:31.300
We're gonna start out
with lot number one.

389
00:26:31.340 --> 00:26:34.220
It's Royal M. Duke. a 2013 registered

390
00:26:34.260 --> 00:26:37.080
English bull offered by
Double G Angus Ranch.

391
00:26:37.180 --> 00:26:40.979
sired by Supreme Domino
out of Miss Domino.

392
00:26:40.980 --> 00:26:43.360
Now we're gonna start the
bidding out at 25.000.

393
00:26:43.380 --> 00:26:46.309
I'm at 25. I'm at 50.

394
00:26:46.310 --> 00:26:47.889
I'm at 55. gonna go 60. at 60 now.

395
00:26:47.890 --> 00:26:51.099
now 5 on 65.000. 65 looking for 70.

396
00:26:51.100 --> 00:26:52.679
75. 75

397
00:26:52.680 --> 00:26:54.760
and now bid at 80. 80.000. 85?

398
00:26:54.770 --> 00:26:55.770
85. now 90. 90?

399
00:26:55.780 --> 00:26:58.000
One phone call. I'll be right back.

400
00:27:00.580 --> 00:27:04.280
We have any little recourse
on the Reservation land?

401
00:27:05.060 --> 00:27:07.799
Civil maybe. but if you're
talking prosecution.

402
00:27:07.800 --> 00:27:09.820
we need friends in the U.S.
Attorney's Office.

403
00:27:12.740 --> 00:27:14.060
Make some.

404
00:27:15.640 --> 00:27:17.000
Hello. Trent.

405
00:27:17.600 --> 00:27:18.700
John.

406
00:27:19.460 --> 00:27:22.340
I wouldn't wish the week you're
having on my mother-in-law.

407
00:27:22.460 --> 00:27:25.400
Well. it's only Tuesday.

408
00:27:26.640 --> 00:27:27.699
50. 60. 60.

409
00:27:27.700 --> 00:27:28.780
Now 70. 70 now.

410
00:27:28.800 --> 00:27:30.780
75. now bid at 80. 80.

411
00:27:31.060 --> 00:27:32.260
John.

412
00:27:33.850 --> 00:27:35.179
This is not the day. Dirk.

413
00:27:35.180 --> 00:27:36.800
The word has it you're hiring.

414
00:27:37.060 --> 00:27:39.700
Cowboys. not criminals.

415
00:27:40.680 --> 00:27:42.260
I can't stop him.

416
00:27:42.640 --> 00:27:43.900
You can.

417
00:27:44.680 --> 00:27:47.700
Jimmy's the only family I have left.

418
00:27:47.890 --> 00:27:50.720
The favor's to me. not to him.

419
00:27:51.480 --> 00:27:53.360
Please.

420
00:27:55.380 --> 00:27:56.880
Please.

421
00:27:57.940 --> 00:27:58.940
All right.

422
00:28:00.850 --> 00:28:02.519
We're gonna do this my way. all right?

423
00:28:02.520 --> 00:28:04.639
- You understand? My way.
- Yeah.

424
00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:06.969
I remember when your
way was the only way.

425
00:28:06.970 --> 00:28:09.760
and the world was better for that.

426
00:28:10.460 --> 00:28:11.940
- Hello. Governor.
- John.

427
00:28:11.960 --> 00:28:13.680
How are you?

428
00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:15.500
Thank you.

429
00:28:17.080 --> 00:28:18.469
Jamie did well at the hearing.

430
00:28:18.470 --> 00:28:21.060
It's easy to do well when
the outcome's decided.

431
00:28:21.160 --> 00:28:22.889
I couldn't hit it if
he didn't tee it up.

432
00:28:22.890 --> 00:28:24.920
and my offer still stands. John.

433
00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:26.769
Yeah. well...

434
00:28:26.770 --> 00:28:28.920
I don't want him in politics.

435
00:28:28.960 --> 00:28:30.820
He's already in politics.

436
00:28:30.890 --> 00:28:33.740
Yeah. with a constituency of one.

437
00:28:37.100 --> 00:28:39.940
How concerned should I be
about this issue on the Res?

438
00:28:41.270 --> 00:28:44.220
It's a new chief showing
off for his voters.

439
00:28:44.300 --> 00:28:45.980
We've all done it.

440
00:28:48.890 --> 00:28:52.099
Well...

441
00:28:52.100 --> 00:28:54.900
we should schedule a lunch.

442
00:28:56.120 --> 00:28:57.720
I could use a lunch.

443
00:29:15.890 --> 00:29:17.929
Sold it to you. 135. Sold it. 135.

444
00:29:36.240 --> 00:29:37.360
You were right.

445
00:29:37.740 --> 00:29:40.160
They're building a city.

446
00:29:40.280 --> 00:29:42.070
Goodnight. Daddy.

447
00:29:42.860 --> 00:29:44.500
Goodnight. sweetheart.

448
00:29:44.860 --> 00:29:46.220
Good to have you home.

449
00:30:27.150 --> 00:30:28.620
That's it.

450
00:30:29.240 --> 00:30:32.280
Come on. That's it.

451
00:30:37.220 --> 00:30:38.420
That's it.

452
00:30:39.200 --> 00:30:40.940
That's it. buddy.

453
00:30:41.080 --> 00:30:42.680
Got tiger stripes on his legs.

454
00:30:44.640 --> 00:30:46.539
You know what that means. don't you?

455
00:30:48.620 --> 00:30:50.180
Spanish blood.

456
00:30:50.240 --> 00:30:51.620
Pure.

457
00:30:52.340 --> 00:30:55.020
One of his ancestors probably
bucked a conquistador

458
00:30:55.100 --> 00:30:57.320
and took to the hills.

459
00:30:57.360 --> 00:30:58.730
You manage to break his spirit.

460
00:30:58.740 --> 00:31:00.490
no horse will serve you better.

461
00:31:00.720 --> 00:31:03.160
He'll serve me just fine
with spirit intact.

462
00:31:03.970 --> 00:31:04.970
Yeah.

463
00:31:05.440 --> 00:31:07.760
I used to think the
same thing at your age.

464
00:31:09.010 --> 00:31:10.740
Hope you prove me wrong.

465
00:31:12.760 --> 00:31:14.820
I didn't know them were your cattle.

466
00:31:15.020 --> 00:31:16.700
Would it have made a difference?

467
00:31:21.200 --> 00:31:23.240
You don't want to be on the
wrong side of this. son.

468
00:31:23.560 --> 00:31:25.860
Yeah. well. the list of things
I don't want is endless.

469
00:31:26.160 --> 00:31:28.080
You telling me what
to do is one of them.

470
00:31:28.120 --> 00:31:29.340
I'm not telling you what to do.

471
00:31:29.350 --> 00:31:31.320
I just don't want you to get in trouble.

472
00:31:31.400 --> 00:31:33.619
Well. if I'd have known there was sides.

473
00:31:33.620 --> 00:31:35.000
I wouldn't have been there at all.

474
00:31:39.300 --> 00:31:40.939
Good lord.

475
00:31:40.940 --> 00:31:43.580
even here the world
just keeps on coming.

476
00:31:44.640 --> 00:31:46.240
Rough week. huh?

477
00:31:46.930 --> 00:31:48.340
Yeah.

478
00:31:48.400 --> 00:31:51.259
One only a grandson could fix.

479
00:31:51.260 --> 00:31:52.900
Thought I'd come see

480
00:31:53.100 --> 00:31:55.740
Tate play in the dirt.
maybe even join him.

481
00:31:59.510 --> 00:32:01.180
He's at Monica's parents.

482
00:32:02.140 --> 00:32:05.780
I guess the early grandpa
gets the worm. huh?

483
00:32:13.920 --> 00:32:16.040
Can I give you some advice. Kayce?

484
00:32:17.660 --> 00:32:19.620
Someday your son's gonna test you.

485
00:32:20.970 --> 00:32:22.830
He's gonna force you to make a decision

486
00:32:22.840 --> 00:32:24.499
that not only determines his future

487
00:32:24.500 --> 00:32:26.760
but your place in it.

488
00:32:27.740 --> 00:32:29.699
I want you to remember
me standing here. son.

489
00:32:29.700 --> 00:32:32.060
before you make that
decision. because this...

490
00:32:32.640 --> 00:32:35.220
this is a consequence of choosing wrong.

491
00:32:39.680 --> 00:32:40.960
Anything else?

492
00:32:41.640 --> 00:32:43.900
I just want to know him. Kayce.

493
00:32:45.300 --> 00:32:47.600
- You know him.
- No. I don't.

494
00:32:48.100 --> 00:32:50.549
I don't. We've met. but
I don't really know him.

495
00:32:50.550 --> 00:32:51.960
And he doesn't know me.

496
00:32:55.220 --> 00:32:58.929
Is it too much to ask that
you help make that happen?

497
00:33:01.350 --> 00:33:03.240
You've always asked too much.

498
00:33:30.720 --> 00:33:33.260
What was he doing here?

499
00:33:33.510 --> 00:33:35.240
Who knows?

500
00:33:35.280 --> 00:33:36.380
Dad!

501
00:33:36.640 --> 00:33:38.520
Is this for me?

502
00:34:15.960 --> 00:34:17.280
You Jimmy?

503
00:34:18.720 --> 00:34:20.300
Dirk Hurdstram's boy?

504
00:34:23.680 --> 00:34:25.360
You alone. Jimmy?

505
00:34:26.740 --> 00:34:28.090
I'll take that as a yes.

506
00:34:37.980 --> 00:34:40.180
You're a two-time loser. Jimmy.

507
00:34:41.180 --> 00:34:43.720
One more felony. and they
throw away the keys.

508
00:34:45.100 --> 00:34:47.280
You know what? You might
do all right in prison.

509
00:34:48.640 --> 00:34:50.220
You got the lips for it.

510
00:34:50.540 --> 00:34:52.670
You're either a servant
or a king in this place.

511
00:34:52.680 --> 00:34:54.680
and I ain't no fucking servant.

512
00:34:55.050 --> 00:34:56.900
No. no.

513
00:35:00.800 --> 00:35:01.960
You're a thief.

514
00:35:03.140 --> 00:35:04.620
Oh. what the fuck. man?

515
00:35:04.760 --> 00:35:06.670
What the fuck. man?

516
00:35:06.680 --> 00:35:07.680
Wait. wait. wait!

517
00:35:07.681 --> 00:35:10.319
Wait. wait. wait! Wait. wait!

518
00:35:10.320 --> 00:35:11.799
Fucking psycho. wait!

519
00:35:11.800 --> 00:35:14.180
Jimmy. I'm gonna give you two choices.

520
00:35:14.560 --> 00:35:17.080
One is I take you and all this shit.

521
00:35:17.160 --> 00:35:18.920
and I drive you down to
the sheriff's office.

522
00:35:19.040 --> 00:35:21.220
and it's good riddance
to your sorry ass.

523
00:35:21.340 --> 00:35:24.360
or you prove that you
deserve another chance.

524
00:35:24.400 --> 00:35:26.459
From what I can see. you don't.

525
00:35:26.460 --> 00:35:28.220
but it ain't up to me.

526
00:35:28.350 --> 00:35:30.760
You're with the Yellowstone?

527
00:35:30.800 --> 00:35:32.640
It's getting cold. Jimmy.

528
00:35:33.800 --> 00:35:35.379
You know what? Fuck it. I'm
taking you to the sheriff's.

529
00:35:35.380 --> 00:35:36.780
- Wait. just...
- Just get up.

530
00:35:39.860 --> 00:35:41.900
Why would John Dutton
give a shit about me?

531
00:35:42.100 --> 00:35:43.840
He doesn't.

532
00:35:46.100 --> 00:35:48.060
But he will.

533
00:35:50.060 --> 00:35:51.799
Now. you be a man about it.

534
00:35:51.800 --> 00:35:53.660
Don't scream.

535
00:36:11.720 --> 00:36:14.040
You know where the ranch is?

536
00:36:16.180 --> 00:36:17.700
You start Monday.

