I'd do it right there around the bend.

808
00:56:40.640 --> 00:56:42.220
That's where they're doing it.

809
00:56:44.340 --> 00:56:45.980
That's your property upstream?

810
00:56:48.980 --> 00:56:50.720
Now. I'm not gonna lie to you.

811
00:56:50.780 --> 00:56:52.880
There's gonna be a severe
impact to your land.

812
00:56:53.520 --> 00:56:55.560
Erosion's my biggest concern.

813
00:56:58.360 --> 00:57:00.430
My biggest concern is a subdivision

814
00:57:00.490 --> 00:57:02.000
sucking on our river.

815
00:57:02.100 --> 00:57:04.100
There's nothing you can do.

816
00:57:04.160 --> 00:57:06.320
On their land. it's their river.

817
00:57:06.870 --> 00:57:09.240
I mean. I can't stop the
river from flowing.

818
00:57:18.540 --> 00:57:20.610
I don't want you to stop it. Ron.

819
00:57:20.680 --> 00:57:22.420
I want you to move it.

820
00:57:34.190 --> 00:57:35.660
How's it going over there?

821
00:57:35.730 --> 00:57:37.176
Oh. hey. we got to make the dressing.

822
00:57:37.200 --> 00:57:38.360
Oh. okay. I'll make it.

823
00:57:42.640 --> 00:57:44.100
How could you give him a D. Monica?

824
00:57:44.170 --> 00:57:45.510
He's your nephew.

825
00:57:45.570 --> 00:57:47.700
The D was a gift. believe me.

826
00:57:48.420 --> 00:57:49.860
What can I say?

827
00:57:49.880 --> 00:57:52.450
Math is not his thing. like his father.

828
00:57:52.510 --> 00:57:53.826
Well. he better make it his thing.

829
00:57:53.850 --> 00:57:55.480
or he's gonna end up like his father.

830
00:57:57.520 --> 00:57:59.690
He's my brother. I can say it.

831
00:57:59.750 --> 00:58:02.390
When I get my steers.
I'm gonna take one.

832
00:58:02.460 --> 00:58:05.160
carve out a porterhouse
the size of a radiator.

833
00:58:07.390 --> 00:58:08.860
They divvying up the cattle?

834
00:58:11.970 --> 00:58:13.470
You don't like it.

835
00:58:13.530 --> 00:58:15.570
maybe you shouldn't
have rounded them up.

836
00:58:17.540 --> 00:58:19.520
They ain't yours to divvy.

837
00:58:23.810 --> 00:58:26.050
What is that one?

838
00:58:28.080 --> 00:58:30.720
It's a Silver Star.

839
00:58:30.780 --> 00:58:32.450
You got one of those?

840
00:58:35.160 --> 00:58:37.000
What do you have to do to win one?

841
00:58:37.690 --> 00:58:40.690
You got to kill someone
to get one of those.

842
00:58:40.760 --> 00:58:42.240
Ain't that right. Kayce?

843
00:58:43.980 --> 00:58:45.560
What about that one?

844
00:58:48.940 --> 00:58:50.470
That's the Navy Cross.

845
00:58:51.910 --> 00:58:54.640
You wouldn't believe what I
had to do to get that one.

846
00:59:01.580 --> 00:59:03.180
What's he doing here?

847
00:59:08.150 --> 00:59:09.860
Well. I hope I'm not intruding.

848
00:59:09.920 --> 00:59:12.359
Of course not. but my
grandfather's not here.

849
00:59:12.360 --> 00:59:14.190
Well. I'm not here to
see your grandfather.

850
00:59:16.800 --> 00:59:19.570
I want to thank you for
helping the other day.

851
00:59:20.070 --> 00:59:22.169
I don't know your father.

852
00:59:22.170 --> 00:59:25.370
I hope it didn't put you in
an uncomfortable position.

853
00:59:26.740 --> 00:59:28.599
Well. if you plan on keeping his cattle.

854
00:59:28.600 --> 00:59:30.580
you'll get to know him real well.

855
00:59:32.310 --> 00:59:35.460
Those are bargaining
chips. a means to an end.

856
00:59:36.350 --> 00:59:38.059
Politicians are like crabs.

857
00:59:38.060 --> 00:59:40.060
We move sideways to go forward.

858
00:59:40.520 --> 00:59:42.390
Well. that won't get
you too far with him.

859
00:59:43.720 --> 00:59:44.980
An honest man?

860
00:59:45.560 --> 00:59:47.670
He says he'll do something.
you're not gonna stop him.

861
00:59:47.690 --> 00:59:49.320
if you call that honest.

862
00:59:50.300 --> 00:59:51.760
I do.

863
00:59:52.200 --> 00:59:54.770
It's a rare thing these days.

864
00:59:54.830 --> 00:59:57.470
What do you want from me?

865
00:59:57.540 --> 00:59:59.120
To help me

866
00:59:59.770 --> 01:00:03.940
understand the man I'm negotiating with.

867
01:00:06.150 --> 01:00:09.580
Well. he's reasonable
till he's provoked.

868
01:00:10.880 --> 01:00:13.250
Then reason don't factor in at all.

869
01:00:15.390 --> 01:00:18.990
Doubt that helps you.
but that's who he is.

870
01:00:19.060 --> 01:00:20.930
It helps.

871
01:00:22.800 --> 01:00:24.730
Thank you for your time.

872
01:00:24.800 --> 01:00:26.630
Have a good evening.

873
01:00:39.530 --> 01:00:41.220
You're not joining him?

874
01:00:41.650 --> 01:00:43.800
You didn't ask me here to hunt.

875
01:00:44.570 --> 01:00:46.240
I'm here to talk cattle.

876
01:00:46.820 --> 01:00:48.800
They don't belong to you.

877
01:00:49.330 --> 01:00:51.579
They don't belong to you either.

878
01:00:51.580 --> 01:00:53.330
They belong to the people now.

879
01:00:53.530 --> 01:00:55.820
Every one of them wears a brand.

880
01:00:55.880 --> 01:00:57.529
If anybody tries to move
them off the Res...

881
01:00:57.530 --> 01:00:59.239
They'll never leave the Res.

882
01:00:59.240 --> 01:01:02.760
We'll use them to raise
calves. wear our brand.

883
01:01:03.450 --> 01:01:05.619
I understand your position. Thomas.

884
01:01:05.620 --> 01:01:07.609
and what you think you need to do...

885
01:01:07.610 --> 01:01:09.529
but I won't allow you to make

886
01:01:09.530 --> 01:01:10.939
victims of the people who elected me

887
01:01:10.940 --> 01:01:13.260
just to appease the
people who elected you.

888
01:01:14.300 --> 01:01:17.610
Your people don't know
the concept of victim.

889
01:01:20.280 --> 01:01:22.200
Let's keep this about cattle.

890
01:01:23.070 --> 01:01:24.960
If you act like a thief. Thomas.

891
01:01:25.530 --> 01:01:27.220
I will treat you like one.

892
01:01:27.490 --> 01:01:29.200
How can you stand there on a ranch

893
01:01:29.220 --> 01:01:31.029
the size of Rhode Island

894
01:01:31.030 --> 01:01:32.580
and accuse me of theft?

895
01:01:33.920 --> 01:01:35.570
Is this your idea of respect?

896
01:01:36.660 --> 01:01:38.840
Letting some crippled old
man ride his lame horse

897
01:01:38.940 --> 01:01:41.360
out toward your half-tame buffalo

898
01:01:41.440 --> 01:01:42.716
so he can pretend to be something

899
01:01:42.740 --> 01:01:45.580
we haven't been in a century?

900
01:01:52.330 --> 01:01:53.880
Whoo!

901
01:01:55.330 --> 01:01:57.100
Look what you've reduced us to.

902
01:02:06.330 --> 01:02:08.039
Here's another one.

903
01:02:10.450 --> 01:02:13.300
You lay everywhere but the coop.

904
01:02:34.420 --> 01:02:35.820
Backstraps.

905
01:02:35.840 --> 01:02:37.580
- Staying for dinner?
- Can't.

906
01:02:37.660 --> 01:02:40.260
Just need a few words with
this young buck here.

907
01:02:40.330 --> 01:02:42.120
Can you give us a minute?

908
01:02:42.160 --> 01:02:44.880
If you can say it to him.
you can say it to me.

909
01:02:45.460 --> 01:02:48.720
Hard to talk about you when
you're standing here. darling.

910
01:02:49.400 --> 01:02:52.260
Come on. Tate. We're
being sent to our room.

911
01:02:54.330 --> 01:02:56.860
The Nation will keep the cattle.

912
01:02:57.560 --> 01:03:00.060
Your father will try to take them back.

913
01:03:00.700 --> 01:03:02.450
He has every right.

914
01:03:03.080 --> 01:03:05.459
We had every right to take them.

915
01:03:05.460 --> 01:03:07.960
so now we will fight.

916
01:03:09.450 --> 01:03:12.119
It's his fight. not mine.

917
01:03:12.120 --> 01:03:14.079
You will be judged

918
01:03:14.080 --> 01:03:16.080
for the actions of your father.

919
01:03:16.660 --> 01:03:20.440
If you do nothing. you will
be judged for that too.

920
01:03:20.700 --> 01:03:22.450
They all will.

921
01:03:22.580 --> 01:03:25.880
Maybe it's best you go
home for a while. eh?

922
01:03:27.080 --> 01:03:28.539
This is my home.

923
01:03:28.540 --> 01:03:30.940
You know what I mean.

924
01:03:33.180 --> 01:03:35.880
I've been nothing but a
friend to everybody here.

925
01:03:37.040 --> 01:03:38.390
If somebody wants me to leave.

926
01:03:38.400 --> 01:03:39.909
you can tell them to come make me.

927
01:03:39.910 --> 01:03:43.480
Pretty silly thing to
say on a reservation.

928
01:03:44.900 --> 01:03:46.460
I don't ask much.

929
01:03:47.330 --> 01:03:49.120
but I'm asking you this.

930
01:03:49.960 --> 01:03:51.360
Go home.

931
01:03:52.260 --> 01:03:54.260
Take care of my granddaughter.

932
01:03:55.910 --> 01:03:57.360
Be good to that boy.

933
01:03:58.290 --> 01:04:01.400
Until they find a cure for human nature.

934
01:04:02.330 --> 01:04:05.260
a man must stand with his people.

935
01:04:09.410 --> 01:04:11.800
And we are not your people.

936
01:04:28.330 --> 01:04:30.620
Hey. Hey. Jimmy!

937
01:04:30.700 --> 01:04:32.330
Let's go. You're late.

938
01:04:32.760 --> 01:04:34.660
Let's go. You're late.

939
01:04:35.520 --> 01:04:37.579
You know how to ride a horse?

940
01:04:37.580 --> 01:04:38.879
Uh...

941
01:04:38.880 --> 01:04:40.739
Figures. Come here. Give me your shit.

942
01:04:40.740 --> 01:04:42.879
Let's go. That there is Ron.

943
01:04:42.880 --> 01:04:44.900
You do whatever the
hell he asks you to do.

944
01:04:45.490 --> 01:04:48.120
Come on. get on. Get on the horse.

945
01:04:48.700 --> 01:04:49.800
I don't...

946
01:04:51.290 --> 01:04:52.700
Get on the horse. Jimmy.

947
01:04:56.560 --> 01:04:57.679
Pull the reins to stop.

948
01:04:57.680 --> 01:04:59.680
Kick him in the belly to go.

949
01:04:59.740 --> 01:05:00.940
All right. let's move.

950
01:05:09.660 --> 01:05:11.080
Both in one night?

951
01:05:13.000 --> 01:05:15.320
Everyone's forgotten
who runs this valley.

952
01:05:16.860 --> 01:05:18.600
So this is how you remind them?

953
01:05:19.620 --> 01:05:21.489
This is not the way to
remind them. It's a...

954
01:05:21.490 --> 01:05:23.040
It's a bad idea.

955
01:05:23.480 --> 01:05:26.240
We don't choose the way. little brother.

956
01:06:06.140 --> 01:06:08.909
Dad. I'm the fastest runner.

957
01:06:08.910 --> 01:06:11.740
I'm bucking. I'm bucking.

958
01:06:12.640 --> 01:06:14.580
And he falls.

959
01:08:11.720 --> 01:08:13.890
This is the last one.

960
01:08:15.040 --> 01:08:18.180
Jimmy. hey. get your ass up here.

961
01:08:19.620 --> 01:08:21.740
- I just saw a trout.
- Shut the fuck up.

962
01:08:21.820 --> 01:08:23.860
Crank this thing until
I tell you to stop.

963
01:08:34.930 --> 01:08:36.430
Holy shit. is this legal?

964
01:08:36.560 --> 01:08:38.429
You're a criminal. What do you care?

965
01:08:38.430 --> 01:08:39.439
I thought the oldest Dutton was gonna

966
01:08:39.440 --> 01:08:40.620
keep me out of trouble.

967
01:08:40.760 --> 01:08:42.559
Getting in trouble's the
only skill you got.

968
01:08:42.560 --> 01:08:43.680
The only difference now is

969
01:08:43.700 --> 01:08:45.120
you ain't gonna get caught.

970
01:08:53.760 --> 01:08:55.720
Start moving it down
to the river. Let's go.

971
01:08:55.800 --> 01:08:58.220
That's good enough.

972
01:09:05.640 --> 01:09:07.940
Start moving it this way now.

973
01:09:10.040 --> 01:09:12.460
Hey. quit looking at fish.

974
01:09:36.180 --> 01:09:39.390
- Hi. Marian. how are you?
- Hi. how are you?

975
01:09:41.720 --> 01:09:43.640
- Hello.
- Hello.

976
01:09:48.800 --> 01:09:51.180
- Sir?
- Thank you.

977
01:09:56.180 --> 01:09:58.460
- How are we all doing here?
- Oh. good!

978
01:09:58.470 --> 01:10:00.120
- It's been a long time.
- Yes.

979
01:10:00.140 --> 01:10:02.320
- Thank you for coming by.
- You look well.

980
01:10:02.360 --> 01:10:03.780
Thank you for joining me.

981
01:10:05.800 --> 01:10:07.080
Bye.

982
01:10:28.860 --> 01:10:31.220
I feel different here.

983
01:10:32.260 --> 01:10:34.360
My skin tingles.

984
01:10:36.000 --> 01:10:38.020
Never felt like this before.

985
01:10:38.640 --> 01:10:40.700
That's because you live in the city.

986
01:10:41.680 --> 01:10:44.620
Cities are the sunsets
of civilization...

987
01:10:45.430 --> 01:10:47.940
monuments to an exhausted landscape.

988
01:10:51.890 --> 01:10:54.680
Man is migratory by nature.

989
01:10:55.720 --> 01:10:59.000
What you're feeling is instinct...

990
01:10:59.550 --> 01:11:02.439
a hunger for new land

991
01:11:02.440 --> 01:11:04.980
that's woven into your DNA.

992
01:11:05.720 --> 01:11:07.840
That's the reason our species survived

993
01:11:07.880 --> 01:11:10.260
when countless others failed.

994
01:11:13.140 --> 01:11:15.400
That tingle

995
01:11:15.550 --> 01:11:19.220
is the sensation of
touching your destiny.

996
01:11:32.640 --> 01:11:36.280
The fuck was that?

997
01:11:36.720 --> 01:11:38.040
Don't know.

998
01:11:55.370 --> 01:11:57.180
- We hold here.
- Hold up here.

999
01:11:57.240 --> 01:11:58.410
They're coming.

1000
01:11:58.480 --> 01:12:00.210
We're in position.

1001
01:12:08.900 --> 01:12:11.520
- Ready?
- Yeah.

1002
01:12:11.590 --> 01:12:13.120
Hold on.

1003
01:12:18.200 --> 01:12:19.800
Get ready.

1004
01:12:20.400 --> 01:12:21.430
They're coming.

1005
01:12:24.040 --> 01:12:25.440
Let 'em.

1006
01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:49.060
Let's get out of here!

1007
01:12:49.130 --> 01:12:51.160
Robert. let's go!

1008
01:12:57.870 --> 01:12:59.600
Lee. get in there.

1009
01:13:00.910 --> 01:13:02.570
Yah. yah!

1010
01:13:08.080 --> 01:13:09.420
Who's that? Is that one of ours?

1011
01:13:09.450 --> 01:13:11.580
- Yah! Yah!
- Hit him with the light.

1012
01:13:14.120 --> 01:13:17.020
- Yah! Yah. yah!
- What the hell's he doing?

1013
01:13:19.390 --> 01:13:20.960
God damn that boy.

1014
01:13:21.030 --> 01:13:22.640
Get behind him.

1015
01:13:24.400 --> 01:13:25.760
Now take us down.

1016
01:13:32.770 --> 01:13:33.860
You see that?

1017
01:13:34.410 --> 01:13:36.040
Jesus Christ!

1018
01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:46.180
No. Hold your fire.

1019
01:13:46.420 --> 01:13:47.940
What do we do now?

1020
01:13:48.620 --> 01:13:50.040
Pull back.

1021
01:13:50.640 --> 01:13:52.960
Pull back. Abort.

1022
01:13:54.690 --> 01:13:56.390
Everybody pull back.

1023
01:14:04.370 --> 01:14:05.970
Put your gun down!

1024
01:14:09.820 --> 01:14:11.580
We got to get the fuck out of here.

1025
01:14:11.640 --> 01:14:13.380
We ain't going anywhere
without our beef.

1026
01:14:13.580 --> 01:14:15.120
Hold them back!

1027
01:14:15.580 --> 01:14:19.120
Get over in front of them!
Hold them back!

1028
01:14:21.390 --> 01:14:22.750
Yah! Yah!

1029
01:14:23.860 --> 01:14:24.960
Yah!

1030
01:14:32.730 --> 01:14:35.000
4 tours in Afghanistan.
and I got to deal

1031
01:14:35.070 --> 01:14:36.900
with this shit in fucking Montana.

1032
01:14:36.970 --> 01:14:39.000
- Wheel us around.
- Jesus Christ. John.

1033
01:14:39.070 --> 01:14:40.950
- we got to get out of here.
- I said wheel us around!

1034
01:14:40.970 --> 01:14:42.910
We've still got men down there.

1035
01:14:42.970 --> 01:14:45.040
Drop us down and push
those bastards back.

1036
01:14:45.110 --> 01:14:46.180
Yes. sir.

1037
01:14:49.350 --> 01:14:50.519
Closer.

1038
01:14:50.520 --> 01:14:51.520
Hang on.

1039
01:15:07.430 --> 01:15:08.680
All right. we're through.

1040
01:15:20.680 --> 01:15:21.910
Keep them moving.

1041
01:15:30.190 --> 01:15:32.500
You want 'em back. come and get 'em!

1042
01:15:40.700 --> 01:15:41.700
Oh!

1043
01:15:57.820 --> 01:15:59.580
I want them back.

1044
01:16:09.930 --> 01:16:11.880
Hang on. okay?

1045
01:16:11.900 --> 01:16:13.530
I'm gonna get you out of here.

1046
01:16:14.830 --> 01:16:17.940
Look at you... you're a man now.

1047
01:16:35.090 --> 01:16:37.000
In case you don't already know.

1048
01:16:37.520 --> 01:16:39.160
there's no such thing as heaven.

1049
01:16:48.330 --> 01:16:49.600
Hey.

1050
01:17:31.020 --> 01:17:32.219
Yes. sir. yeah. I hear you.

1051
01:17:32.220 --> 01:17:33.280
Give me four mounted agents

1052
01:17:33.290 --> 01:17:35.379
and four agents on ATVs
out there right now.

1053
01:17:35.380 --> 01:17:36.410
Yes.

1054
01:17:37.950 --> 01:17:39.460
I hear... okay.

1055
01:17:40.250 --> 01:17:41.600
Okay. thank you.

1056
01:17:42.150 --> 01:17:43.650
Thank you.

1057
01:17:45.640 --> 01:17:46.919
All right. state police are sending

1058
01:17:46.920 --> 01:17:48.530
a chopper out to look for him.

1059
01:17:54.330 --> 01:17:56.100
Tell them to hold off.

1060
01:17:56.170 --> 01:17:57.500
I found him.

1061
01:18:25.460 --> 01:18:26.980
Give me the reins.

1062
01:18:27.630 --> 01:18:29.140
Give me the reins.

1063
01:18:29.730 --> 01:18:31.070
All right.

1064
01:18:32.140 --> 01:18:33.540
Go straight to Jamie.

1065
01:18:33.550 --> 01:18:35.840
Tell him everything while
it's fresh. all right?

1066
01:19:11.080 --> 01:19:12.640
What happened?

1067
01:19:37.900 --> 01:19:39.600
We'll just...

1068
01:19:43.020 --> 01:19:44.599
We'll just...

1069
01:19:44.600 --> 01:19:46.600
we'll just rest here a bit.

1070
01:19:48.150 --> 01:19:49.780
Then we can...

1071
01:19:51.920 --> 01:19:55.650
We can pick a spot together. huh?

1072
01:19:57.960 --> 01:19:59.560
How's that sound?

1073
01:20:36.460 --> 01:20:38.940
Okay.

1074
01:21:06.890 --> 01:21:08.330
Mama?

1075
01:21:08.520 --> 01:21:10.660
Go back to your room.

1076
01:21:11.320 --> 01:21:12.530
Now.

1077
01:23:04.820 --> 01:23:06.560
Fuck.

1078
01:23:07.280 --> 01:23:08.879
A dispute over cattle

1079
01:23:08.880 --> 01:23:11.330
between tribal police. BLM officers.

1080
01:23:11.340 --> 01:23:13.850
and members of Montana's
livestock association

1081
01:23:13.860 --> 01:23:15.199
turned deadly last night...

1082
01:23:15.200 --> 01:23:16.649
- Turn it down.
- Leaving three men dead.

1083
01:23:16.650 --> 01:23:18.060
The FBI...

1084
01:23:20.580 --> 01:23:22.620
What did Kayce tell you?

1085
01:23:23.150 --> 01:23:25.760
The usual. nothing.

1086
01:23:28.000 --> 01:23:29.640
I should have seen this coming.

1087
01:23:30.680 --> 01:23:32.860
How could you know he
wanted the cattle that bad?

1088
01:23:33.150 --> 01:23:35.020
He didn't want the cattle.

1089
01:23:36.980 --> 01:23:38.400
He wanted this.

1090
01:23:38.420 --> 01:23:41.339
The FBI and Bureau of
Indian Affairs agents

1091
01:23:41.340 --> 01:23:43.930
are investigating two of
the deaths as murders.

1092
01:23:43.940 --> 01:23:45.640
and though jurisdictional issues

1093
01:23:45.680 --> 01:23:48.080
will certainly complicate
the investigation.

1094
01:23:48.090 --> 01:23:49.920
the U.S. Attorney's Office is pledging

1095
01:23:49.970 --> 01:23:51.820
every available resource.

1096
01:23:53.340 --> 01:23:56.009
I'll have a senate hearing
on this next month.

1097
01:23:56.010 --> 01:23:58.700
You have the full weight
of my office behind you.

1098
01:23:59.100 --> 01:24:01.660
Thank you. Senator. We're gonna need it.

1099
01:24:21.240 --> 01:24:22.609
Dad.

1100
01:24:22.610 --> 01:24:23.860
It's time.

1101
01:24:31.820 --> 01:24:32.980
Boys.

1102
01:25:18.740 --> 01:25:20.400
Let us pray.

1103
01:25:23.570 --> 01:25:25.520
"Men and brethren.

1104
01:25:25.620 --> 01:25:28.960
let me freely speak unto
you of the patriarch David.

1105
01:25:28.980 --> 01:25:31.649
that he is both dead and buried... "

1106
01:26:26.600 --> 01:26:28.900
Amen.

1107
01:27:35.280 --> 01:27:36.899
He's one hell of a horse.

1108
01:27:36.900 --> 01:27:39.820
Yeah.

1109
01:27:41.740 --> 01:27:45.660
Ain't got the breeding of your
stud. but he has a heart.

1110
01:27:46.820 --> 01:27:48.220
I know. I saw.

1111
01:27:51.040 --> 01:27:52.780
He would have died for me.

1112
01:27:54.820 --> 01:27:56.600
He almost did.

1113
01:27:59.080 --> 01:28:01.040
You want to stay for supper?

1114
01:28:04.380 --> 01:28:05.920
You can put him in the barn.

1115
01:28:05.940 --> 01:28:07.160
No.

1116
01:28:08.260 --> 01:28:10.280
I brought him for you.

1117
01:28:10.680 --> 01:28:12.340
You can put him in the barn.

1118
01:29:49.640 --> 01:29:52.780
I deserve to know what happened. Kayce.

1119
01:29:55.400 --> 01:29:57.240
He was my brother.

1120
01:30:06.650 --> 01:30:08.240
What happened?

1121
01:30:11.620 --> 01:30:13.500
Baby. why won't you talk to me?

1122
01:30:56.480 --> 01:30:59.140
He's never looked at me
the way he looked at Lee.

1123
01:31:02.700 --> 01:31:04.740
And he never will.

1124
01:31:17.280 --> 01:31:19.180
I need you more than ever.

1125
01:31:20.610 --> 01:31:22.040
You have me.

1126
01:31:25.040 --> 01:31:26.600
Can you stay for a while?

1127
01:31:27.140 --> 01:31:28.879
I'm not going anywhere.

1128
01:31:28.880 --> 01:31:30.600
Just tell me who to fight.

1129
01:31:34.030 --> 01:31:35.400
Everyone.
